WEBVTT

00:02.127 --> 00:03.377
<i>Yaga.</i>

00:03.378 --> 00:05.504
<i>What is that?</i>

00:05.505 --> 00:07.881
Artificial cursed corpses can act

00:07.882 --> 00:12.010
more independently than other puppetry.

00:12.011 --> 00:14.096
But their power source, cursed energy,

00:14.097 --> 00:16.890
is consumed from what a sorcerer provides.

00:16.891 --> 00:19.560
That thing's cursed energy is its own.

00:19.561 --> 00:21.312
It can even replenish itself.

00:23.398 --> 00:26.608
The higher-ups have now designated you
as a special grade,

00:26.609 --> 00:30.071
and are formally moving
to detain you indefinitely.

00:31.031 --> 00:34.825
<i>If you intentionally created that thing,</i>

00:34.826 --> 00:38.704
then you could easily command an army.

00:38.705 --> 00:41.207
Answer me, Yaga.

00:42.709 --> 00:46.420
You truly don't know

00:46.421 --> 00:47.964
how to make it, do you?

00:51.009 --> 00:51.843
Yes.

00:53.136 --> 00:54.429
<i>Masamichi.</i>

00:55.680 --> 00:58.974
<i>Everyone is worried about you.
They say you've been down lately.</i>

00:58.975 --> 01:01.144
<i>I see.</i>

01:02.979 --> 01:04.938
So I told them,

01:04.939 --> 01:07.859
if you're not feeling well,
you just need cheering up.

01:10.570 --> 01:11.529
I see.

01:12.280 --> 01:13.740
I'm a genius, right?

01:14.407 --> 01:15.784
Yes.

01:16.701 --> 01:20.580
Takeru, I'm sorry, but I won't be able
to come back for a while.

01:21.164 --> 01:22.999
Tell everyone that for me.

01:23.541 --> 01:25.375
Another trip?

01:25.376 --> 01:28.128
Yes. A long one.

01:28.129 --> 01:32.800
It's all right.
Master Tengen protects this forest.

01:32.801 --> 01:36.387
Your mom will come visit you again too.

01:37.931 --> 01:40.558
You'll be fine even without me.

01:44.145 --> 01:45.438
Masamichi…

01:46.481 --> 01:48.900
It's lonely without you.

01:54.239 --> 01:56.281
Is this really okay, Kusakabe?

01:56.282 --> 01:59.660
Don't go saying I helped you.

01:59.661 --> 02:02.705
You being captured was just bait
to draw Yaga out.

02:03.998 --> 02:06.084
I owe that man.

02:07.919 --> 02:09.796
Go. Now.

02:11.089 --> 02:12.674
You're sure about this?

02:13.591 --> 02:15.884
That isn't your nephew.

02:15.885 --> 02:18.054
It's something carrying
your nephew's information.

02:18.680 --> 02:20.889
If you cling to the dead forever,

02:20.890 --> 02:24.686
you can't live in the future, right?

02:25.979 --> 02:29.106
But, my sister can't live on…

02:29.107 --> 02:32.527
Without Takeru supporting her,
she can't live on.

02:36.823 --> 02:40.535
Masamichi, that woman is my mom, right?

02:41.578 --> 02:44.414
Yes. You figured it out.

02:46.499 --> 02:48.293
I thought so.

02:51.421 --> 02:52.672
I'm a genius, right?

03:11.316 --> 03:12.817
I'm sorry, but…

03:13.568 --> 03:15.027
I know.

03:15.028 --> 03:18.865
The existence of a fully autonomous
cursed corpse can't be made public.

03:19.574 --> 03:21.325
Takeru can't live with his mother.

03:21.326 --> 03:22.743
I'm sorry.

03:22.744 --> 03:24.996
Why are you apologizing?

03:26.247 --> 03:27.957
Thank you.

03:29.042 --> 03:32.462
Really, thank you.

03:33.922 --> 03:38.051
Where are you going without
your cursed corpse, Principal Yaga?

03:39.344 --> 03:40.845
To see my son.

03:41.471 --> 03:46.017
Let me tell you the only way
you can survive this death sentence.

03:46.643 --> 03:51.314
Reveal the method for creating
an autonomous artificial cursed corpse.

03:52.815 --> 03:56.069
You're so bold, now that Satoru is gone.

04:26.683 --> 04:27.558
Principal.

04:28.559 --> 04:31.812
Stand down, and I'll handle the rest.

04:31.813 --> 04:32.647
Understood.

04:34.148 --> 04:36.108
You copy the soul's information

04:36.109 --> 04:39.486
from the body.

04:39.487 --> 04:43.741
Then you input that information
into the cursed corpse's core.

04:47.120 --> 04:49.496
<i>But that alone isn't enough.</i>

04:49.497 --> 04:52.499
<i>You must place three compatible souls</i>

04:52.500 --> 04:54.043
<i>into a single core.</i>

04:55.044 --> 05:01.091
and have them constantly observe
one another.

05:01.092 --> 05:02.969
Only then does the soul stabilize,

05:03.553 --> 05:05.429
and an ego is born.

05:05.430 --> 05:07.931
After about three months,

05:07.932 --> 05:10.684
it begins self-replenishing cursed energy.

05:10.685 --> 05:12.103
Why…

05:13.813 --> 05:15.898
tell me this now?

05:16.691 --> 05:21.863
Why not sooner? Why did I survive?

05:22.739 --> 05:25.741
It's a curse,

05:25.742 --> 05:27.577
Principal Gakuganji.

05:28.161 --> 05:32.457
A curse from me to you.

05:36.210 --> 05:37.503
Masamichi!

05:47.555 --> 05:51.476
Why won't you fight? Don't you hate me?

05:52.685 --> 05:55.188
I'm not bound by that stuff.

05:56.064 --> 05:59.442
You and Masamichi weren't on bad terms.

06:00.234 --> 06:04.197
To me, you're like a knife
lying on the ground.

06:06.032 --> 06:09.493
But remember this…

06:09.494 --> 06:13.247
Even a panda can cry…

07:51.679 --> 07:54.055
Kinji Hakari is currently
in Tochigi Prefecture,

07:54.056 --> 07:58.436
running gambling matches
at the old multi-storey car park site.

07:59.228 --> 08:00.645
Gambling matches?

08:00.646 --> 08:03.023
Sorcerers beating each other up.

08:03.024 --> 08:05.192
Then the spectators are…

08:05.193 --> 08:07.195
Mostly non-sorcerers.

08:08.070 --> 08:10.030
That's a direct violation of Secrecy,

08:10.031 --> 08:11.615
<i>Article Eight of the regulations.</i>

08:11.616 --> 08:12.949
SECRECY

08:12.950 --> 08:16.286
Some of the fighters
will likely be curse users.

08:16.287 --> 08:18.039
Be careful.

08:21.250 --> 08:22.210
Why change clothes?

08:22.835 --> 08:26.046
Hakari got suspended
after fighting with the higher-ups.

08:26.047 --> 08:28.174
He's still actively breaking regulations.

08:28.925 --> 08:32.093
If they realize we're with Jujutsu High,
he might run.

08:32.094 --> 08:34.680
It's like cops and robbers.

08:36.432 --> 08:38.517
So we are on Jujutsu High's side now?

08:38.518 --> 08:40.060
The morality is a bit gray,

08:40.061 --> 08:42.938
but from Hakari's point of view,
we're definitely the bad guys.

08:42.939 --> 08:45.357
Is he even the type who would help us?

08:45.358 --> 08:49.778
Hard to say.
The upperclassmen all say he's a scumbag.

08:49.779 --> 08:53.366
But even Okkotsu says
Hakari's stronger than him.

08:54.367 --> 08:56.285
We absolutely need his strength.

08:56.869 --> 08:58.120
Go home, brat.

08:58.704 --> 09:00.748
This isn't a hangout spot.

09:01.332 --> 09:03.542
On the count of three, turn back.

09:03.543 --> 09:06.294
Any other choice and I'll punch you.

09:06.295 --> 09:07.879
We need money.

09:07.880 --> 09:10.091
Let me enter the gambling matches
being held here.

09:13.219 --> 09:14.512
Rule number one.

09:15.263 --> 09:17.974
"You do not speak
about the gambling matches."

09:18.724 --> 09:23.270
Now, answer. Who told you?
I'll punch you after that.

09:23.271 --> 09:25.523
I don't know his name. I killed him.

09:26.107 --> 09:27.775
About a month ago.

09:28.317 --> 09:30.278
There was a loudmouth loser, remember?

09:30.903 --> 09:33.656
Kondo disappeared a month ago.

09:34.240 --> 09:36.075
I'll fill that spot.

09:36.826 --> 09:40.370
Or I could drop you
right in front of the bookie.

09:40.371 --> 09:41.371
<i>I see…</i>

09:41.372 --> 09:44.124
<i>If we ask to see him right away,
they'll get suspicious.</i>

09:44.125 --> 09:46.418
- Yes?
<i>- And we can't even say "Hakari."</i>

09:46.419 --> 09:48.838
- No proof.
<i>- Better keep my mouth shut.</i>

09:49.672 --> 09:51.173
That's far enough.

09:51.924 --> 09:53.593
The boss bookie gave the okay.

09:54.176 --> 09:56.720
We'll slot him into today's seed match.

09:56.721 --> 09:59.557
But the one entering is that one.

10:02.059 --> 10:05.979
<i>Works for me.
Itadori is the better fit for the match.</i>

10:05.980 --> 10:07.856
No. I'm going.

10:07.857 --> 10:10.109
Boss says you're not worth betting on.

10:10.818 --> 10:12.945
If you don't like it, deal is off.

10:14.238 --> 10:16.407
Fine. That works.

10:17.116 --> 10:20.619
Fushiguro, that was risky.
That bluff was too much.

10:20.620 --> 10:21.871
Not really.

10:22.622 --> 10:26.708
If curse users are competing too,
there should be turnover.

10:26.709 --> 10:27.959
More importantly…

10:27.960 --> 10:29.544
Yes. Someone is here.

10:29.545 --> 10:30.462
UNDER CONSTRUCTION. 100 METERS AHEAD

10:30.463 --> 10:32.757
If they were watching us
on the security cameras,

10:33.424 --> 10:36.301
there's a good chance Hakari is in there.

10:36.302 --> 10:38.554
Itadori, enter the match
and investigate from the inside.

10:39.138 --> 10:43.016
While you do,
I'll infiltrate that car park… Maybe.

10:43.017 --> 10:46.144
- Maybe?
- They're probably letting me run free.

10:46.145 --> 10:49.147
If my infiltration gets exposed,
we lose all credibility.

10:49.148 --> 10:51.150
Then we'll never get a chance
to talk to Hakari.

10:51.859 --> 10:54.612
Then we go all-out.

10:55.196 --> 10:57.447
That's the real last resort.

10:57.448 --> 10:58.948
We're here to ask Hakari

10:58.949 --> 11:02.285
to help us.

11:02.286 --> 11:05.122
I want to avoid anything
that will ruin our relationship.

11:05.748 --> 11:08.793
I don't think we should act tonight.

11:09.335 --> 11:12.003
But I don't want to waste time

11:12.004 --> 11:13.714
before Tsumiki's declaration deadline.

11:14.465 --> 11:17.676
It's 17:00 on the 10th.

11:18.344 --> 11:20.261
So, we've got nine days left.

11:20.262 --> 11:23.349
It took longer than I thought
to get here too.

11:23.933 --> 11:27.353
That's why I'll infiltrate tonight
and feel him out,

11:27.978 --> 11:31.815
but if it looks bad, I'll pull back.
That's why it's "maybe."

11:31.816 --> 11:32.775
Got it.

11:34.860 --> 11:39.197
Two rules. Don't run.
Don't use cursed techniques.

11:39.198 --> 11:43.201
Why? I don't mind if they do
use cursed techniques.

11:43.202 --> 11:45.245
Most of the spectators are non-sorcerers.

11:45.246 --> 11:49.582
They can't see it.
Invisible fights don't hype the crowd.

11:49.583 --> 11:50.918
Then why "don't run"?

11:51.502 --> 11:54.712
It means fight
where the crowd can see you.

11:54.713 --> 11:56.881
So it's all about the audience.

11:56.882 --> 11:59.301
Of course. It's business.

12:00.261 --> 12:01.387
What is the boss like?

12:02.930 --> 12:03.764
Curious?

12:04.765 --> 12:05.724
Yes.

12:06.642 --> 12:08.978
- You'll know when you meet him.
- I can meet him?

12:10.479 --> 12:12.564
There are two kinds of matches.

12:12.565 --> 12:16.693
No-script straight-up bouts like today,
and fixed matches with a script.

12:16.694 --> 12:19.071
The boss writes the scripts.

12:19.655 --> 12:22.241
If you put on a good show here,
he might call for you.

12:23.284 --> 12:25.952
So basically, I just need to win big
and get attention.

12:25.953 --> 12:28.205
That sounds simpler.

12:38.132 --> 12:40.926
That's your opponent.

12:43.637 --> 12:46.640
First time I saw him, I lost it too.

12:48.517 --> 12:50.102
He's basically a crowd-puller.

12:52.938 --> 12:55.607
All right, let's get started tonight!

12:55.608 --> 12:58.610
The no-script, straight-up
Fight Club Tournament!!

12:58.611 --> 13:02.322
<i>Your commentator, John Bobby as always!</i>

13:02.323 --> 13:05.533
<i>Here we go with a killer match-up!</i>

13:05.534 --> 13:08.787
<i>A sudden assassin!
Triangles, then squares!</i>

13:09.371 --> 13:14.126
<i>The dangerous fireball boy! Yuji Itadori!</i>

13:14.710 --> 13:17.086
<i>Standing Panda, sitting Panda,</i>

13:17.087 --> 13:19.839
<i>walking Panda is literally Panda!</i>

13:19.840 --> 13:22.842
<i>Panda!</i>

13:22.843 --> 13:23.718
BATTLE ARENA - 2ND FLOOR

13:23.719 --> 13:28.848
<i>Now then! Feel the excitement?</i>

13:28.849 --> 13:31.768
I can feel the excitement cooling off.

13:31.769 --> 13:33.853
Why, Kinji?

13:33.854 --> 13:37.233
"Luck" only matters if it's being tested.

13:37.816 --> 13:39.860
A bet where you can see the win is boring.

13:40.569 --> 13:44.614
There aren't many tough guys out there
who can beat Panda.

13:44.615 --> 13:46.658
<i>Oh! Here it is!</i>

13:46.659 --> 13:49.620
- Maybe not.
- What?

13:54.208 --> 13:56.418
Panda, did you find Hakari?

13:57.211 --> 13:58.294
No.

13:58.295 --> 13:59.463
LIGHT TOUCH

14:03.050 --> 14:05.635
We know each other, so he's not on guard.

14:05.636 --> 14:07.053
But he's avoiding me.

14:07.054 --> 14:08.222
LIGHT TOUCH

14:11.976 --> 14:15.229
There's also one more third-year,
but their technique is the problem.

14:24.572 --> 14:26.990
You're hiding
that you're from Jujutsu High, right?

14:26.991 --> 14:28.284
Yes.

14:29.785 --> 14:32.705
Good. You know what to do next, right?

14:38.669 --> 14:43.965
Oh, wow! This is absolutely
the best bout of my commentary career!

14:43.966 --> 14:47.010
<i>I've only been doing this
for six months, though!</i>

14:47.011 --> 14:48.387
Hey!

14:51.891 --> 14:52.558
TAP

14:54.727 --> 14:55.477
LIGHT TOUCH

14:58.105 --> 15:00.941
LIGHT TOUCH

15:05.404 --> 15:06.280
LIGHT TOUCH

15:12.620 --> 15:16.248
<i>And the winner is Itadori!</i>

15:17.583 --> 15:19.918
What a punch!

15:19.919 --> 15:23.797
I can't move! Animal welfare groups
won't stay quiet about this!

15:24.715 --> 15:25.632
<i>Your acting sucks.</i>

15:25.633 --> 15:29.469
<i>When the tournament is over,
bring Itadori up to the roof.</i>

15:29.470 --> 15:31.512
- What?
<i>- He'll make it to the end anyway.</i>

15:31.513 --> 15:36.935
<i>And he was consciously moving in 3D
to entertain the upper-floor crowd.</i>

15:36.936 --> 15:39.103
<i>I can write a good script with that.</i>

15:39.104 --> 15:40.022
<i>Like I always tell you…</i>

15:41.607 --> 15:44.693
Strike while the iron is hot.

15:45.277 --> 15:47.528
Quit it, you sound like an idiot.

15:47.529 --> 15:51.074
<i>Yes, sir.
But what do we do about the other kid?</i>

15:51.075 --> 15:55.578
Keep watching him.
I'll send Kirara to security later too.

15:55.579 --> 15:56.537
What?

15:56.538 --> 16:01.000
This is getting noisy.
The last time it got this noisy

16:01.001 --> 16:04.671
was when my ex kept racking up
charges on monthly payments.

16:04.672 --> 16:06.589
Stop talking about your ex.

16:06.590 --> 16:07.883
JUJUTSU HIGH 3RD YEAR-KIRARA HOSHI

16:09.969 --> 16:11.427
I see.

16:11.428 --> 16:13.973
So Itadori and Hakari
might actually make contact.

16:14.765 --> 16:16.182
Why haven't you been able

16:16.183 --> 16:18.726
to meet Hakari yet?

16:18.727 --> 16:21.479
Right… I know where he is.

16:21.480 --> 16:23.815
The monitoring room on the roof.

16:23.816 --> 16:26.193
But I can't get close.

16:26.777 --> 16:28.111
You can't get close?

16:28.112 --> 16:31.322
Even if you walk right up to the door,
you can't get closer to him.

16:31.323 --> 16:34.784
<i>The sensation
is kind of like Satoru's technique.</i>

16:34.785 --> 16:37.996
It's probably Kirara's technique, but…

16:37.997 --> 16:42.125
Kirara?
The other third-year was a guy, right?

16:42.126 --> 16:43.376
He's a guy.

16:43.377 --> 16:47.839
Does that only happen
when Kirara is in the monitoring room?

16:47.840 --> 16:49.298
No idea.

16:49.299 --> 16:54.012
I figured it's better to be "crowd Panda"
than push too hard and have him run away.

16:54.013 --> 16:56.098
I'm glad you two showed up.

16:56.932 --> 16:59.225
Do you think Itadori can convince him?

16:59.226 --> 17:03.396
It will be rough.
But it might come down to timing.

17:03.397 --> 17:08.026
Itadori's upbeat, likable personality
should pair well with Hakari.

17:08.027 --> 17:09.986
But he's terrible at lying, right?

17:09.987 --> 17:14.365
More like, he has no concept of lying
in the first place.

17:14.366 --> 17:18.578
Once Itadori gets into
the monitoring room,

17:18.579 --> 17:21.164
I can seize control of this hideout,

17:21.165 --> 17:24.250
and buy those two time to talk.

17:24.251 --> 17:25.168
No, that's…

17:25.169 --> 17:27.670
Relax. I'll just put them to sleep.

17:27.671 --> 17:30.215
I've already got the camera positions
and blind spots memorized.

17:30.924 --> 17:32.133
How many guards?

17:32.134 --> 17:36.138
Four at the entrance.
Two on each floor besides the roof.

17:39.058 --> 17:40.100
We can do it.

17:40.684 --> 17:43.686
<i>The concern is Kirara's technique.</i>

17:43.687 --> 17:45.813
<i>Yes, can't help that.</i>

17:45.814 --> 17:49.817
<i>If it can warp Itadori out
or bring reinforcements in,</i>

17:49.818 --> 17:52.111
<i>then we give up on persuading Hakari.</i>

17:52.112 --> 17:55.740
Yuu-chan, you're still a first-year?
So young.

17:55.741 --> 17:56.575
Yuu-chan?

17:57.367 --> 17:59.328
Kinji repeated a year in middle school.

18:00.120 --> 18:03.665
- You look weirdly happy about that.
- Yes.

18:04.458 --> 18:07.336
Kinji is getting fired up again,
for the first time in a while.

18:08.420 --> 18:12.216
And I love a fired-up Kinji.

18:17.596 --> 18:21.099
Itadori. If someone told you,
"Just do one thing for one hour a day

18:21.100 --> 18:26.229
and you'll be making 10,000 yen a month."
Would you believe it?

18:26.230 --> 18:31.067
What? Depends what that one thing is.

18:31.068 --> 18:36.239
But to learn that one thing, you would
have to buy a course for 20,000 yen.

18:36.240 --> 18:39.367
What? I wouldn't buy that.

18:39.368 --> 18:41.828
Yes. You have good intuition.

18:41.829 --> 18:43.914
It's a classic scam.

18:44.414 --> 18:48.417
The scammer pretends to be rich,
sells you a way to get rich,

18:48.418 --> 18:50.294
and takes your money.

18:50.295 --> 18:52.547
Logically, it's obvious,

18:52.548 --> 18:55.466
but there are plenty of idiots
who still fall for it.

18:55.467 --> 18:59.303
Why? Because of heat.

18:59.304 --> 19:00.263
Heat?

19:00.264 --> 19:03.016
Both sides have it.

19:03.559 --> 19:07.271
That "I'm going to change my life
right here" kind of heated passion.

19:08.063 --> 19:11.274
People get swept up in it
and make bad calls.

19:11.275 --> 19:14.778
But without heat,
people can't even fall in love.

19:15.362 --> 19:17.573
I love heat.

19:18.407 --> 19:22.077
A more direct exchange of heat.
Know what that is?

19:23.328 --> 19:24.163
Gambling?

19:27.457 --> 19:29.960
Knew you would get it.

19:30.752 --> 19:32.588
Living is gambling.

19:33.213 --> 19:36.674
A ton of women dumped me
because they hate gambling,

19:36.675 --> 19:39.052
but they've got it backwards.

19:40.095 --> 19:42.847
In this society, the ones who can't go big

19:42.848 --> 19:45.976
and the ones who don't know when to fold
get shaken off.

19:46.560 --> 19:49.770
There's no such thing
as a person who never gambles.

19:49.771 --> 19:52.940
Gambling isn't what they hate.

19:52.941 --> 19:55.568
It's "losing" and "ruin."

19:55.569 --> 19:58.613
Some people just want a calm life, though…

19:58.614 --> 20:01.074
Don't know any of them.

20:01.867 --> 20:04.119
I love heat.

20:04.828 --> 20:08.290
Heat is gambling. Gambling is life.

20:08.874 --> 20:10.876
And love is control.

20:11.710 --> 20:16.298
Someday, through Fight Club,
I want to control this country's heat.

20:17.007 --> 20:21.260
With cursed spirits acknowledged
and the higher-ups barely functioning,

20:21.261 --> 20:23.347
now is the chance to expand.

20:24.056 --> 20:25.973
Crush every obstacle,

20:25.974 --> 20:28.226
ride the coming revisions
to the jujutsu regulations,

20:28.227 --> 20:31.521
and get Fight Club recognized publicly.

20:32.314 --> 20:36.026
Anyway,
I've got excellent pieces on the board.

20:37.611 --> 20:38.654
Including you, Itadori.

20:39.821 --> 20:42.616
Want to get swept up in my heat?

20:43.992 --> 20:46.578
Boss, we need to talk--

20:58.840 --> 21:01.175
Itadori. Want something to drink?

21:01.176 --> 21:04.637
Oh, anything's fine.
As long as it's not alcohol.

21:04.638 --> 21:06.973
What, you can't handle it?

21:06.974 --> 21:09.267
That's not the issue. I'm underage.

21:09.268 --> 21:11.811
You don't look like the type
who cares about that.

21:11.812 --> 21:14.939
Did you know?
Satoru Gojo is a lightweight too.

21:14.940 --> 21:17.400
What? Gojo who?

21:17.401 --> 21:20.194
And what do you mean "too"?
It's not like I…

21:20.195 --> 21:22.239
Listen.

21:29.997 --> 21:33.624
What kind of sorcerer
doesn't know Satoru Gojo?

21:33.625 --> 21:36.795
Why would you pretend you didn't know?
Are you…

21:43.302 --> 21:44.886
an agent of Jujutsu High?

21:52.185 --> 21:55.147
Listen!

21:56.898 --> 21:59.650
Calls from Kirara's number

21:59.651 --> 22:01.778
mean something is wrong.

22:03.864 --> 22:04.947
Listen!

22:04.948 --> 22:06.324
No!

22:06.325 --> 22:07.909
I've cooled off now!

23:41.753 --> 23:44.964
<i>If we can persuade this person,
negotiating with Hakari will be easier!</i>

23:44.965 --> 23:46.340
<i>Wait, Kirara!</i>

23:46.341 --> 23:48.509
<i>- I have something to say!
- Don't lay a hand on him.</i>

23:48.510 --> 23:49.969
<i>I have to say it here!</i>

23:49.970 --> 23:52.138
<i>Please. We don't have time.</i>

23:52.139 --> 23:54.140
<i>Kinji is in danger!</i>

23:54.141 --> 23:55.934
NEXT EPISODE
